The 3Cpro assay was a 28-min, room temperature procedure. Detector antibodies were mixed with the sample and added to the antibody coated optical surface. Binding of 3Cpro was visualized through an enzymatic reaction that deposited mass on the surface, generating a thickness change. The thin film optics of the surface transduced the thickness increase into a visible color change (Fig. 1
). We determined the limit of detection for purified recombinant HRV2 3Cpro (Fig. 2
A). The visual limit of detection was 12 pM, or 0.3 fmol/assay.
